      <title>Call ChatGPT from any phone with OpenAI’s new 1-800 voice service</title>
      <author>
          Benj Edwards
        </author>
      <link>https://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2024/12/openai-launches-free-phone-hotline-to-let-anyone-call-chatgpt/</link>
      <comments>https://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2024/12/openai-launches-free-phone-hotline-to-let-anyone-call-chatgpt/#comments</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">0d8adb07194ef0cc781854e50fe92be0139459d3</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 18 Dec 2024 18:42:40 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;         1-800-CHATGPT telephone number lets any US caller talk to OpenAI's assistant—no smartphone required.       &lt;/p&gt;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img width="1152" height="648" src="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/toy_robot_phone2-1152x648.jpg" class="intro-image absolute min-w-full min-h-full h-auto object-cover" alt="Photo of two tin toy robots with a vintage telephone handset receiver." loading="eager" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/toy_robot_phone2-1152x648.jpg 1152w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/toy_robot_phone2-640x360.jpg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/toy_robot_phone2-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/toy_robot_phone2-768x432.jpg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/toy_robot_phone2-384x216.jpg 384w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/toy_robot_phone2-980x551.jpg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/toy_robot_phone2.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1152px) 100vw, 1152px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;                       &lt;span class="caption-credit mt-2 text-xs"&gt;           Credit:                        &lt;a class="caption-credit-link text-gray-400 no-underline hover:text-gray-500" href="https://www.gettyimages.com/detail/photo/robots-on-the-phone-close-up-royalty-free-image/1050703168"               target="_blank"&gt;                      Charles Taylor via Getty Images                        &lt;/a&gt;                   &lt;/span&gt;           &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;                                                         &lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, OpenAI launched a 1-800-CHATGPT (1-800-242-8478) telephone number that anyone in the US can call to talk to ChatGPT via voice chat for up to 15 minutes for free. The company also says that people outside the US can send text messages to the same number for free using WhatsApp.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Upon calling, users hear a voice say, "Hello again, it's ChatGPT, an AI assistant. Our conversation may be reviewed for safety. How can I help you?" Callers can ask ChatGPT anything they would normally ask the AI assistant and have a live, interactive conversation.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;During a livestream demo of "Calling with ChatGPT" during Day 10 of "&lt;a href="https://arstechnica.com/ai/2024/12/openai-teases-12-days-of-mystery-product-launches-starting-tomorrow/"&gt;12 Days of OpenAI&lt;/a&gt;," OpenAI employees demonstrated several examples of the telephone-based voice chat in action, asking ChatGPT to identify a distinctive house in California and for help in translating a message into Spanish for a friend. For fun, they showed calls from an iPhone, a flip phone, and a vintage rotary phone.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;figure class="ars-wp-img-shortcode id-2067570 align-center"&gt;     &lt;div&gt;                         &lt;img width="1024" height="576" src="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/chatgpt_number_demo-1024x576.jpg" class="center large" alt="OpenAI developers demonstrate calling 1-800-CHATGPT during a livestream on December 18, 2024." decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/chatgpt_number_demo-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/chatgpt_number_demo-640x360.jpg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/chatgpt_number_demo-768x432.jpg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/chatgpt_number_demo-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/chatgpt_number_demo-384x216.jpg 384w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/chatgpt_number_demo-1152x648.jpg 1152w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/chatgpt_number_demo-980x551.jpg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/chatgpt_number_demo-1440x810.jpg 1440w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/chatgpt_number_demo.jpg 1583w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /&gt;                   &lt;/div&gt;           &lt;figcaption&gt;         &lt;div     class="caption font-impact dusk:text-gray-300 mb-4 mt-2 inline-flex flex-row items-stretch gap-1 text-base leading-tight text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-300"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-icon bg-[left_top_5px] w-[10px] shrink-0"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-content"&gt;       OpenAI developers demonstrate calling 1-800-CHATGPT during a livestream on December 18, 2024.                &lt;span class="caption-credit mt-2 text-xs"&gt;           Credit:                       OpenAI                    &lt;/span&gt;           &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/figcaption&gt;       &lt;/figure&gt;  &lt;p&gt;OpenAI says the new features came out of an internal OpenAI "hack week" project that a team built just a few weeks ago. The company says its goal is to make ChatGPT more accessible if someone does not have a smartphone or a computer handy.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;During the livestream, an OpenAI employee explained that voice calls are limited to 15 minutes, after which users are prompted to return to their regular ChatGPT interface (website, mobile, or desktop app). The voice calling feature is built on OpenAI's &lt;a href="https://openai.com/index/introducing-the-realtime-api/"&gt;Realtime API&lt;/a&gt;, while the WhatsApp text interface uses GPT-4o mini.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
